3. JUDGMENT CHECKS

   Spec accretion — NONE FOUND.
   DoctorStatus/DoctorCheck/DoctorReport are consumed by runDoctor() return values
   and read in doctor-smoke.js (checks[n].status, report.ok, report.summary, etc.).
   The new "doctor" capability descriptor's `surface` and `reason` fields are read
   at runtime in capability-registry.ts (lines 514, 532, 542, 557–563, 587).
   No declared-but-never-read types introduced.

   Test quality — ALL PASS THE REVERT TEST.
   - registry-corrupt-fail-closed-smoke.js: the five assert.throws calls fail if
     the silent-fallback catch blocks are restored.
   - robustness-failclosed-smoke.js part C (16 concurrent scheduler creates,
     asserts all N tasks survive) provably fails without the withFileLock wrapper.
   - doctor-smoke.js: the five pinned behaviors (shape, read-only, no-agent warn,
     unwritable-home fail, --json mode) all fail if doctor.ts is reverted.
   - sched-policy-validation-smoke.js: assert.throws on non-numeric flag fails
     without the Number.isFinite guard.
   - bump-version-idempotent-smoke.js and parity-doc-sync-smoke.js: gate guards,
     not trivial assertions.

   Direction — SERVES NORTH STAR.
   - Track A (5-min demo): `cw doctor` eliminates the most common new-user
     friction (misconfigured agent, bad Node version, unwritable state surfacing
     mid-run as a confusing error). Self-documenting CLI (14 previously-hidden
     commands now listed by `cw help`) directly reduces onboarding time.
   - Track B (failure-recovery): fail-closed hardening on all authoritative
     durable-state loaders (archive/provenance overlays, repos.json, queue,
     scheduling policy) and scheduler write serialisation are correctness fixes
     that make failure-recovery paths reliable.

   Tag message — SATISFIES REQUIREMENT.
   User-visible capability stated in one concrete sentence (first two lines above).

   FreeBSD discipline — NO VIOLATIONS.
   - POLA: no flag, exit code, or output shape changed for VALID input. The
     corrupt-input path change (silent-fallback → throw) is a bug fix, not a
     POLA violation; Rule 4 (fail closed) explicitly supersedes silent-fallback.
   - Mechanism not policy: `cw doctor` is marked surface:"cli-only" by design;
     no vendor-specific logic enters core.
   - Rule of Silence: doctor report is data (stdout); skipped-worker diagnostic
     goes to stderr; --json surface is clean, stable, machine-parseable.
   - Fail closed: explicit hardening across scheduling-policy, archive overlay,
     provenance overlay, queue, repos.json, worker scope, and MCP line buffer.
   - Man pages: `doctor` documented in the generated cli-mcp-parity.7.md (row
     at line 83, rationale at line 288); also referenced in agent-delegation-
     drive.7.md, durable-state-and-locking.7.md, execution-backends.7.md, and
     others. Parity-doc sync verified by parity-doc-sync-smoke (gate step 4).
   - style(9): scheduler changes are mechanical lock-wrapper additions; reclamation
     carve-out is a behavior-preserving code movement. No reformatting of
     untouched code.

